summary: This is a brief email from a US Attorney's Office representative, likely from the Southern District of New York (SDNY), responding to an inquiry and copying Assistant U.S. Attorneys (AUSAs) working on the Jeffrey Epstein case. It indicates the AUSAs are willing to discuss the case.
keyFacts: The email is dated August 30, 2019, shortly after Jeffrey Epstein's death in custody on August 10, 2019.
The sender is from the U.S. Attorney's Office, likely the Southern District of New York (SDNY), which was handling the Epstein prosecution.
The email copies multiple Assistant U.S. Attorneys (AUSAs) who were working on the Epstein case, indicating they were open to communication regarding the matter.
The document identifier 'EFTA00079931' suggests it is part of a larger document set related to the Epstein case.
